<dl>
<dt>Notes</dt>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><span class="citation wikicite" id="endnote_1"><b><a href="#ref_1">^1</a></b></span> Also reached number-one on the <a href="UK_Singles_Chart" title="UK Singles Chart">UK Singles Chart</a></li>
<li><span class="citation wikicite" id="endnote_2"><b><a href="#ref_2">^2</a></b></span> Was simultaneously number-one that week on the UK Singles Chart</li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=List_of_UK_R&B_Chart_number-one_singles_of_2008&action=edit&section=1.php.html" title="Edit section: Year-end statistics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Year-end_statistics">Year-end statistics</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Best selling number one R&amp;B single - "American Boy" by Estelle featuring Kanye West, sales of 460,474</li>
<li>Best selling number one R&amp;B artist - Rihanna, combined sales of 1,190,305</li>
<li>Most weeks at number one (single, consecutive) - "No Air" by Jordin Sparks and Chris Brown, 6 weeks</li>
<li>Most weeks at number one (single, non-consecutive) - "Don't Stop the Music" by Rihanna and "American Boy" by Estelle featuring Kanye West, both 5 weeks</li>
<li>Most weeks at number one (artist, consecutive) - Jordin Sparks and Chris Brown, 6 weeks</li>
<li>Most weeks at number one (artist, non-consecutive) - Rihanna, 16 weeks</li>
</ul>
